Y
{\rm E}[Y] = {\rm E}\sum_{i=1}^n B_i = \sum_{i=1}^n {\rm E}[B_i] = \sum_{i=1}^n p = np.
{\rm Var}[Y] = \sum_{i=1}^n {\rm Var}[B_i] = \sum_{i=1}^n p(1-p) = np(1-p).
\begin{align*} M_Y(t) &= {\rm E}[e^{Yt}] = {\rm E}\left[\exp \sum_{i=1}^n B_i t \right] \\ &= {\rm E}\left[ \prod_{i=1}^n e^{B_i t} \right] \\ &= \prod_{i=1}^n {\rm E}[e^{B_i t}] \\ &= \prod_{i=1}^n M_{B_i}(t) \\ &= (1 - p + pe^t)^n. \end{align*}
